    {
      "assetId": "math.arith.fraction-equivalence/teaching_note/1",
      "kind": "teaching_note",
      "conceptId": "math.arith.fraction-equivalence",
      "title": "Student State Matrix",
      "content": "| State | Entry Condition | Protocol |\n|-------|----------------|----------|\n| S0 | No prior exposure to equivalent fractions | Protocol A — full CPA, 5 TAs |\n| S1 | Generates equivalents by ×2 or ×3 procedurally; cannot explain why value is preserved | Protocol B — conceptual grounding, 3 TAs |\n| S2 | Carries MC-1 (additive thinking) and/or MC-2 (simplified-only) | Protocol C — schema repair, 3–4 TAs |\n| S6 | Correct understanding; low confidence on non-obvious equivalents or verification tasks | Protocol D — scaffolded practice, 3 TAs |\n| S9 | Second-language learner; visual-dominant; vocabulary gaps (numerator/denominator) | Protocol E — visual-first, 3 TAs |\n\n---",
      "localKey": null,
      "language": "en",
      "refs": [
        "MC-1",
        "MC-2"
      ],
      "span": {
