    {
      "assetId": "math.arith.fraction-equivalence/teaching_note/2",
      "kind": "teaching_note",
      "conceptId": "math.arith.fraction-equivalence",
      "title": "Diagnostic Battery",
      "content": "Run DB-1 through DB-3 in sequence. Stop when entry state is confirmed.\n\n---\n\n**DB-1 — Prior Exposure Check**\n\nQuestion: \"Can you tell me what equivalent fractions are? Give an example.\"\n\nResponse taxonomy:\n```\n{ stimulus: \"Two fractions that name the same amount; e.g. 1/2 = 2/4\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:CORRECT\" }\n\n{ stimulus: \"Mentions 'same' or names a correct pair but cannot say why they're equal\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:PARTIAL\" }\n\n{ stimulus: \"Doesn't know, gives wrong example, or says 'fractions with the same top or bottom'\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:INCORRECT\" }\n\n{ stimulus: \"No response\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:NO_RESPONSE\" }\n```\n\nSIGNAL:CORRECT → run DB-2 (test procedure depth)  \nSIGNAL:PARTIAL → S1 candidate; run DB-2  \nSIGNAL:INCORRECT → S0; route to Protocol A  \nSIGNAL:NO_RESPONSE → S0; route to Protocol A\n\n---\n\n**DB-2 — Procedure and Misconception Probe**\n\nQuestion: \"Make a fraction equivalent to 3/5 by multiplying. Now — is 4/6 equivalent to 3/5? How do you know?\"\n\nResponse taxonomy:\n```\n{ stimulus: \"Multiplies correctly (e.g. 6/10); states 4/6 ≠ 3/5 via cross-multiplication or decimal\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:CORRECT\" }\n\n{ stimulus: \"Generates 6/10 but cannot verify 4/6 ≠ 3/5, or says 4/6 = 3/5 because '+ 1 to each'\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:PARTIAL\" }\n\n{ stimulus: \"Produces 4/6 from 3/5 by adding 1 to numerator and denominator\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:INCORRECT\", mc_id: \"MC-1\" }\n\n{ stimulus: \"Generates correct equivalent but says 4/6 is 'also equivalent' because it looks close\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:INCORRECT\", mc_id: \"MC-2-risk\" }\n```\n\nSIGNAL:CORRECT → run DB-3 (confidence calibration)  \nSIGNAL:PARTIAL → S1; route to Protocol B  \nSIGNAL:INCORRECT (MC-1) → S2 with MC-1 active; route to Protocol C  \nSIGNAL:INCORRECT (MC-2-risk) → S2 with MC-2 active; route to Protocol C\n\n---\n\n**DB-3 — Confidence Calibration**\n\nQuestion: \"How confident are you — on a scale of 1–5 — that you could explain to a friend *why* multiplying top and bottom by the same number doesn't change the fraction's value?\"\n\nResponse taxonomy:\n```\n{ stimulus: \"4–5: gives clear multiplicative explanation (×k/k = 1; multiplying by 1 preserves value)\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:CORRECT\" }\n\n{ stimulus: \"2–3: understands it works but uncertain about the explanation\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:PARTIAL\" }\n\n{ stimulus: \"1: says 'I just know the rule'; no conceptual anchor\",\n  signal: \"SIGNAL:INCORRECT\" }\n```\n\nSIGNAL:CORRECT → verified understanding; administer assessment battery to confirm mastery  \nSIGNAL:PARTIAL → S6 overlay likely; route to Protocol D  \nSIGNAL:INCORRECT (with prior correct procedure) → S6; route to Protocol D\n\n---",
      "localKey": null,
      "language": "en",
      "refs": [
